 tools. Whilst spatially resolved\nspectroscopy is likely to remain out of reach for this particular galaxy, we\nestimate HARMONI's performance limits in this regime from our findings. This\nstudy demonstrates how instrument simulators such as HSIM can be used to\nquantify instrument performance and study observational biases on kinematics\nretrieval; and shows the potential of making observational predictions from\ncosmological simulation output data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Feb 2016 22:00:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-23"}
